<text top="77" left="83" width="426" height="54" font="1">Breach Notifications</text>
<text top="175" left="66" width="962" height="40" font="9">The GDPR has a requirement that you notify the subjects of </text>
<text top="218" left="66" width="899" height="40" font="9">data collection if there is a breach in the security of their </text>
<text top="261" left="66" width="80" height="40" font="9">data </text>
<text top="304" left="66" width="895" height="40" font="9">• <i>“Where a breach is likely to result in a high risk to the </i></text>
<text top="348" left="107" width="907" height="40" font="11"><i>rights and freedoms of individuals, you must notify those </i></text>
<text top="391" left="107" width="312" height="40" font="11"><i>concerned directly.”</i></text>
<text top="434" left="66" width="899" height="40" font="9">• <i>“Failing to notify a breach when required to do so can </i></text>
<text top="477" left="107" width="895" height="40" font="11"><i>result in a significant fine up to 10 million Euros or 2 per </i></text>
<text top="520" left="107" width="457" height="40" font="11"><i>cent of your global turnover.”</i></text>
</page>
