<text top="150" left="49" width="596" height="35" font="2">What are the core principles of UK GDPR?</text>
<text top="188" left="157" width="875" height="35" font="13">Six principles that say how and when you can handle personal </text>
<text top="225" left="49" width="61" height="35" font="13">data</text>
<text top="263" left="49" width="1002" height="35" font="2">What are the rights of the subjects of data gathering activities under the </text>
<text top="301" left="49" width="108" height="35" font="2">GDPR?</text>
<text top="339" left="157" width="687" height="35" font="13">Eight rights in total each with specific implications</text>
<text top="377" left="49" width="920" height="35" font="2">What are the implications of the Data Protection Act for Computer </text>
<text top="414" left="49" width="323" height="35" font="2">Scientists in particular?</text>
<text top="452" left="157" width="798" height="35" font="13">You need to keep personal data safe or you are liable for </text>
<text top="490" left="49" width="129" height="35" font="13">damages</text>
<text top="528" left="49" width="844" height="35" font="2">What is Privacy Shield and why do we need to care about it?</text>
<text top="566" left="157" width="834" height="35" font="13">A body that allows date outside the EU that may show what </text>
<text top="603" left="49" width="70" height="35" font="13">data </text>
<text top="603" left="157" width="461" height="35" font="13">control outside the EU will be like</text>
